sql:
SELECT artist_name
FROM artists
ORDER BY artist_name ASC;

external_knowledge:
- "sowing more than one seed" metaphorically refers to having more than one album;
- "the garden of their respective musical genres" represents the genres and the albums within them;
- "the size of their sown gardens" translates to the count of albums each artist has in a genre.

- "flower" metaphorically represents the reviews given by users; 
- "blooming the most brightly" is a metaphor indicating the review with the highest visibility due to upvotes; 
- "sun's rays of upvotes" symbolizes the upvotes, which are like the sunlight nourishing the flowers, indicating that the upvotes are the measure of popularity and positive reception.

sql:
SELECT review
FROM ratings
WHERE upvotes = (SELECT MAX(upvotes) FROM ratings);

SELECT title, track_list
FROM albums
WHERE title = 'Green Day';

SELECT role
FROM artist_albums
WHERE artist_id IS NOT NULL;

SELECT a.artist_name, al.title
FROM artists a
LEFT JOIN albums al ON a.artist_id = al.artist_id;

external_knowledge:
